    <text>
      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Department of Science and Art |South Kensington, London, S.W.</placeName>
                    <date>7 February 1857</date>
                    <salute>My dear Professor</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>I like very much your idea of displaying cottage ornament &amp; we will adopt it.</p>
                  <p>1. We shall have a Chamber of Horrors displaying the bad taste of Cottage Ornament from painted parrots to a bright Queen sitting on a throne with ball, sceptre &amp;c.</p>
                  <p>2. An adjoining Compartment with good Cottage Ornament, showing how at similar prices good as well as bad taste could be cultivated.</p>
                  <p>Will you kindly illustrate as an Exhibition the Style of Cottage Ornament of your own district &amp; as these wonderful Works of art are not very Expensive, we will furnish you with 20/- for the purpose in the first place-</p>
                  <p>Yours sincly | Lyon Playfair</p>
                  <p>N.B. The marketable price of the article should always be stated</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
